photon experiment.

00:04:20.870 --> 00:04:26.360 align:middle line:84%
It was conducted in 1997,
the University of Geneva.

00:04:26.360 --> 00:04:30.620 align:middle line:84%
It was reported to over
3,400 journalists, educators,

00:04:30.620 --> 00:04:33.680 align:middle line:84%
scientists, and engineers
in more than 40 countries

00:04:33.680 --> 00:04:37.100 align:middle line:84%
on Friday, July
25th of that year.

00:04:37.100 --> 00:04:39.950 align:middle line:84%
So let me share with you
how this experiment worked.

00:04:39.950 --> 00:04:42.170 align:middle line:84%
And we can take the
ideas from the experiment

00:04:42.170 --> 00:04:45.350 align:middle line:84%
itself and apply them to
our lives in the simulation

00:04:45.350 --> 00:04:47.390 align:middle line:90%
that we're living right now.

00:04:47.390 --> 00:04:49.640 align:middle line:10%
So in the experiment,
the scientists

00:04:49.640 --> 00:04:54.250 align:middle line:10%
began with a particle of
energy that forms atoms.

00:04:54.250 --> 00:04:56.210 align:middle line:10%
It's called a photon.

00:04:56.210 --> 00:05:00.380 align:middle line:10%
And they wanted to have
two identical photons,

00:05:00.380 --> 00:05:05.420 align:middle line:10%
so they took one and broke it
into two separate photons that

00:05:05.420 --> 00:05:07.790 align:middle line:10%
have precisely the
same properties.

00:05:07.790 --> 00:05:11.630 align:middle line:84%
They have to because they are
from the same original photon.

00:05:11.630 --> 00:05:15.500 align:middle line:84%
This is why they are
called the twin photons.

00:05:15.500 --> 00:05:19.820 align:middle line:84%
Once they had two
identical photons,

00:05:19.820 --> 00:05:23.030 align:middle line:84%
they placed them into
a specialized device

00:05:23.030 --> 00:05:26.720 align:middle line:84%
that was connected to
fiber optic cables that

00:05:26.720 --> 00:05:29.270 align:middle line:90%
ran in opposite directions.

00:05:29.270 --> 00:05:34.070 align:middle line:84%
From the device, one cable ran
seven miles in one direction.

00:05:34.070 --> 00:05:37.630 align:middle line:84%
One cable ran seven miles
in the other direction.

00:05:37.630 --> 00:05:44.330 align:middle line:84%
And they took these photons and
they fired them simultaneously

00:05:44.330 --> 00:05:49.250 align:middle line:84%
in the two directions so
that when each photon reached

00:05:49.250 --> 00:05:52.160 align:middle line:84%
the maximum distance from
the place where it began,

00:05:52.160 --> 00:05:54.570 align:middle line:90%
they were 14 miles apart.

00:05:54.570 --> 00:05:57.320 align:middle line:84%
But this is where
the experiment began

00:05:57.320 --> 00:06:02.480 align:middle line:84%
because, once those photons
were isolated, 14 miles apart,

00:06:02.480 --> 00:06:08.390 align:middle line:84%
scientists began to demonstrate
that what happened to one

00:06:08.390 --> 00:06:13.090 align:middle line:84%
photon was perceived and was
happening to the other photon

00:06:13.090 --> 00:06:15.600 align:middle line:90%
at exactly the same time.

00:06:15.600 --> 00:06:18.470 align:middle line:84%
So for example, if they would
change the magnetic charge

00:06:18.470 --> 00:06:22.010 align:middle line:84%
on one photon, the magnetic
charge in the other photon

00:06:22.010 --> 00:06:24.975 align:middle line:84%
changed as if it were
having the same experience,

00:06:24.975 --> 00:06:28.200 align:middle line:84%
as if it were the one
that had been tweaked.

00:06:28.200 --> 00:06:31.800 align:middle line:84%
Or if the rotation of one
of the photons was shifted,

00:06:31.800 --> 00:06:33.510 align:middle line:84%
the other one
acted as if it were

00:06:33.510 --> 00:06:36.660 align:middle line:90%
the one that had been changed.

00:06:36.660 --> 00:06:40.140 align:middle line:84%
They were communicating,
and the mystery, the mystery

00:06:40.140 --> 00:06:42.105 align:middle line:90%
was, how are they communicating?

00:06:42.105 --> 00:06:44.130 align:middle line:90%
And here's why it's a mystery.

00:06:44.130 --> 00:06:47.730 align:middle line:84%
Because we're told in
our world of physics

00:06:47.730 --> 00:06:52.200 align:middle line:84%
that information can only travel
as fast as the speed of light

00:06:52.200 --> 00:06:53.480 align:middle line:90%
and no faster.

00:06:53.480 --> 00:06:58.050 align:middle line:10%
All right, so the scientists
were using atomic clocks

00:06:58.050 --> 00:07:03.330 align:middle line:10%
to find out how much time lapsed
between the time one photon

00:07:03.330 --> 00:07:06.446 align:middle line:10%
was tweaked and when the
other photon responded.

00:07:06.446 --> 00:07:08.070 align:middle line:84%
And to their amazement,
what they found

00:07:08.070 --> 00:07:11.100 align:middle line:84%
is the amount of time
that lapsed was zero.

00:07:11.100 --> 00:07:13.230 align:middle line:90%
There was no time lapse.

00:07:13.230 --> 00:07:15.570 align:middle line:90%
The change was instantaneous.

00:07:15.570 --> 00:07:17.160 align:middle line:84%
And they said, well,
how can that be?

00:07:17.160 --> 00:07:21.090 align:middle line:84%
Because the information must
get from one to the other.

00:07:21.090 --> 00:07:23.130 align:middle line:84%
It cannot travel faster
than the speed of light.

00:07:23.130 --> 00:07:25.680 align:middle line:90%
How can this be simultaneous?

00:07:25.680 --> 00:07:28.052 align:middle line:84%
And this led them
to the understanding

00:07:28.052 --> 00:07:30.510 align:middle line:84%
that is relevant for everything
that we're doing here right

00:07:30.510 --> 00:07:32.850 align:middle line:90%
now in our simulation.

00:07:32.850 --> 00:07:37.320 align:middle line:84%
The photons did not need to
communicate from one place

00:07:37.320 --> 00:07:39.300 align:middle line:84%
to another, as
conventional thinking says.

00:07:39.300 --> 00:07:41.540 align:middle line:90%
It's a linear way of thinking.

00:07:41.540 --> 00:07:43.990 align:middle line:84%
They weren't
communicating, saying,

00:07:43.990 --> 00:07:46.620 align:middle line:84%
hey, I just had my
charge changed over here,

00:07:46.620 --> 00:07:49.080 align:middle line:84%
and now you need to
change yours over there.

00:07:49.080 --> 00:07:54.810 align:middle line:84%
What happened was, even though
they were physically separated,

00:07:54.810 --> 00:07:58.740 align:middle line:84%
because they had
once been combined,

00:07:58.740 --> 00:08:02.345 align:middle line:84%
they were still connected
on an energetic level.

00:08:02.345 --> 00:08:05.250 align:middle line:84%
And this is what the
experiment is showing.

00:08:05.250 --> 00:08:07.800 align:middle line:84%
It is called entanglement,
this relationship

00:08:07.800 --> 00:08:10.500 align:middle line:90%
is called quantum entanglement.

00:08:10.500 --> 00:08:13.830 align:middle line:84%
And what it says to
us is that matter,

00:08:13.830 --> 00:08:18.660 align:middle line:84%
